article.description: Corbin Moore had a double-double and Pepperdine ran off the final eight points to defeat UTSA 70-64 in overtime Saturday.
article.headline: Corbin Moore key as Pepperdine holds on against UTSA
article.linkText: Moore key as Pepperdine holds on against UTSA
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Corbin Moore had a double-double and Pepperdine ran off the final eight points to defeat UTSA 70-64 in overtime Saturday. Moore had 14 points and 14 rebounds for the Waves (3-2), who snapped a two-game losing streak. Taylor Darby also had a double-double, with 11 points and 11 rebounds. Jordan Baker scored 14 points, Nikolas Skouen 11 and Joshua Lowery 10. Kannon Burrage scored 18 for the Roadrunners (3-3), who dropped their home opener Moore's 3-pointer with 10 seconds left forced overtime. Then, after UTSA scored the first two points of the extra session, Moore tied it with a jumper. Lowery put the Waves ahead, and Caleb Willis scored the last four points to close it out. Neither team shot well. Pepperdine went 25-for-60 (41.7 percent) and UTSA 20-for-57 (35.1 percent). The Waves had a 45-38 advantage on the boards.
